ThAr_HARPS_lines.dat
     The APF uses the same lamps as the HARPS spectrometer
     by construction. Most lines come from a paper on
     the lines in the spectrometer.
     The spectrometer has a gap of ~25 A between 5305 and 5330
     which is filled in with a theory paper (RNS14) which uses
     Lovis and Pepe (2007) to calibrate the Th atom model.
  -- Lovis and Pepe (2007) A&A, 468, 1115
  -- RNS14 is Redman, Nave, & Sansonetti (2014) ApJS, 211, 4